# 🚀 DevOps Project: Jenkins-DooD News Pipeline

This project involves a **Flask-based web application** that is containerized with **Docker**. The application is managed through a **CI/CD pipeline** running in **Jenkins**, which is itself containerized. The pipeline utilizes **Docker-outside-of-Docker (DooD)** by mounting the host's Docker socket, allowing Jenkins to build, stop, and run containers directly on the host engine.

The application fetches and displays **Ynet news headlines** on port 5000. The pipeline handles **building the Docker image, automated container replacement, and health validation** using shell-based testing. Sensitive configurations and repository access are securely handled using **Jenkins Credentials**.

---
## Clone the repo
```
git clone https://github.com/sagitab/First-Project-Sela.git
cd First-Project-Sela
```
---
## Start the app
# start the jenkins container
```
docker-compose up -d
```
# do push to git to activate the jenkins pipeline
